The Chef really has some of the best fwends around. Back when The Chef found out his book sales were quite low, he schemed up a few ways to drive sales but also placed a few phone calls to close friends to ask for advice. The support from fwends meant so much to The Chef he made it the subject of his second bloven mitt ceweal box theater performance.

It’s finally here everyone!!! We all had such a good time Saturday night watching The Chef’s Malinea slide show!! Please enjoy the slideshow as if you were there that night, Cheffy put so much thought and work into this recreation of the event (he even had sprigs of rosemary and thyme roasting nearby for smell!) and it would mean so much to him for people to enjoy the “meal” as if they were there!
.
.
Also big thanks to all chefs friends and attendees it meant so much to him to have all his friends in one space!
.
.

.

.
.
We love you Nina!!! And thank you miss @jackietohn , we have a sneaking suspicion you made this happen for Cheffy. You’re his best bestie.
.
.
And thank you again @zennioptical cheffy gets compliments on his glasses almost daily!!
.

.

Y’all Cheffy had a blamazing blirfday!!! We spent most of the day picking up litter (notice his le pickerrrrrr 3000 birthday gift from last year!?) and ended with a nice little cake and lots of singing and dancing. I showed Chef all of your messages of love and he was completely overwhelmed (as was the tiny team!) we can’t thank y’all enough for your support and love for Cheffy. We want to make all his dreams come true and couldn’t do it without the cheffer nation of support!!! 
.
Cheffy said one day he hopes his birthday becomes one big international litter cleanup party year after year so people can see how fun it is to clean and take care of our little earth home. How cool would that be!?!?
.

.
Happy Monday cheffers!!!
